# Lamb Meatballs

> This #persian meatball recipe is fast and filling, but most importantly...looks impressive to others.

Turn on Broiler Oven

- Garlic | 3 cloves | Minced
- Salt | “pinch” | 

Crush into paste

## Prepare the Meat

> Use a large mixing bowl

Add half garlic paste

- Lamb | 1 lb | 
- Salt | 1 tsp | 
- Cumin Seeds | 2 tsp | 
- Hot Sauce | 1/2 tsp | 
- Black Pepper | “to taste” | 
- Chile Powder | 1/2 tsp | 
- Scallion | 1 count | 
- Parsley | 2 tbsp | 

Mix above ingredients

## Shape the Meatballs

Oil rimmed baking tray

Make 1.5-inch meatballs and place 1-2 inches apart

Broil for 8 minutes

## Dipping Sauce

> This is the Tahini dipping sauce

- Plain Yogurt | 1/4 cup | 
- Tahnini | 1/4 cup | 
- Lemon |  | Juice only
- Salt | 1/4 tsp | 

Remaining garlic paste

Mix above ingredients

